article.headline: N. Illinois 86, Indiana St. 79
article.story: DEKALB, Ill. -- Mike DiNunno and Darion Anderson scored 27 points each to lead Northern Illinois to an 86-79 victory over Indiana State on Tuesday night. DiNunno and Anderson combined for 10 3-pointers for Northern Illinois (2-1). Sean Kowal added 10 points for the Huskies. Northern Illinois jumped out to a 20-8 lead, capped by a 3-pointer by DiNunno. The Huskies led 38-33 at halftime. Indiana State (0-1) reached 55-53 with 13:04 left in the second half, but the Huskies pulled away with a 15-3 run over the next seven minutes. Rashad Reed led Indiana State with 21 points, including five 3-pointers. Aaron Carter added 15 points, Jay Tunnell had 14 points and Josh Crawford chipped in 13 points for the Sycamores.
